  "culturalTip": "In Korea, guests at a wedding usually give money as a gift to the couple. Guests can hand in their envelopes filled with cash at the reception desk of the wedding venue. If a guest would like to give a physical item, then they give it privately before or after the ceremony. However, most Korean couples leave for their honeymoon directly after the ceremony, so if you have a gift that is to be used while on honeymoon, you may give it to the couple at the wedding.",
